                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 4992/3.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Rockhill</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-03-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 20, 1907</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Rockhill states that the Chinese Government in reply to inquiry says that
                    “all American criminals guilty of an ordinary offense who have taken refuge in
                    Chinese territory, can of course be extradited, except those guilty of political
                    offenses.” Mr. Rockhill adds that the Chinese Government will take action in the
                    case submitted upon a statement of the exact nature of the crime and the
                    presentation of written evidence.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
